#. <section class="sutta" id="mn136"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn136:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 136"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 136"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn136:0.2"
msgid "Mahākammavibhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Analysis of Deeds"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.207"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn136:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā samiddhi araññakuṭikāyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Samiddhi was staying in a wilderness hut."

msgctxt "mn136:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho potaliputto paribbājako jaṅghāvihāraṃ anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno "
"yenāyasmā samiddhi tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā samiddhinā saddhiṃ "
"sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then as the wanderer Potaliputta was going for a walk he came up to "
"Venerable Samiddhi and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "mn136:2.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho potaliputto paribbājako āyasmantaṃ samiddhiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn136:2.4"
msgid ""
"“sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso samiddhi, samaṇassa gotamassa sutaṃ, sammukhā "
"paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Samiddhi, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the "
"ascetic Gotama:"

msgctxt "mn136:2.5"
msgid "‘moghaṃ kāyakammaṃ moghaṃ vacīkammaṃ, manokammameva saccan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Deeds by way of body and speech are done in vain. Only mental deeds are "
"real.’"

#. VAR: Atthi ca sā → atthi cesā (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:2.6"
msgid "Atthi ca sā samāpatti yaṃ samāpattiṃ samāpanno na kiñci vediyatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"And: ‘There is such an attainment where the one who enters it does not feel "
"anything at all.’”"

#. VAR: mā hevaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, avaca → idaṃ vākyaṃ syā1-3, kaṃ potthakesu
msgctxt "mn136:2.7"
msgid ""
"“Mā hevaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, avaca; mā hevaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, avaca; mā "
"bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi. Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ. Na hi bhagavā "
"evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“Don’t say that, Reverend Potaliputta, don’t say that! Don’t misrepresent "
"the Buddha, for misrepresentation of the Buddha is not good. And the Buddha "
"would not say this."

msgctxt "mn136:2.8"
msgid "‘moghaṃ kāyakammaṃ moghaṃ vacīkammaṃ, manokammameva saccan’ti."
msgstr ""

# Quote marks in MS are incorrect. Here, as shown by the avuso, samiddhi is directly addressing Potaliputta.
#. VAR: Atthi ca kho → atthi ceva kho (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:2.9"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi ca kho sā, āvuso, samāpatti yaṃ samāpattiṃ samāpanno na kiñci "
"vediyatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"But, reverend, there is such an attainment where the one who enters it does "
"not feel anything at all.”"

msgctxt "mn136:2.10"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ pabbajitosi, āvuso samiddhī”ti?"
msgstr "“Reverend Samiddhi, how long has it been since you went forth?”"

msgctxt "mn136:2.11"
msgid "“Na ciraṃ, āvuso, tīṇi vassānī”ti."
msgstr "“Not long, reverend: three years.”"

#. VAR: nāma evaṃnavo bhikkhu → nāmevaṃ navo bhikkhu (bj) | navakena bhikkhunā (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:2.12"
msgid ""
"“Ettha dāni mayaṃ there bhikkhū kiṃ vakkhāma, yatra hi nāma evaṃnavo bhikkhu "
"satthāraṃ parirakkhitabbaṃ maññissati."
msgstr ""
"“Well now, what are we to say to the senior mendicants, when even such a "
"junior mendicant imagines their Teacher needs defending?"

msgctxt "mn136:2.13"
msgid ""
"Sañcetanikaṃ, āvuso samiddhi, kammaṃ katvā kāyena vācāya manasā kiṃ so "
"vediyatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"After doing an intentional deed by way of body, speech, or mind, reverend, "
"what does one feel?”"

msgctxt "mn136:2.14"
msgid ""
"“Sañcetanikaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, kammaṃ katvā kāyena vācāya manasā dukkhaṃ "
"so vediyatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“After doing an intentional deed by way of body, speech, or mind, reverend, "
"one feels suffering.”"

msgctxt "mn136:2.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho potaliputto paribbājako āyasmato samiddhissa bhāsitaṃ neva "
"abhinandi nappaṭikkosi;"
msgstr ""
"Then, neither approving nor dismissing Samiddhi’s statement, Potaliputta"

msgctxt "mn136:2.16"
msgid "anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.208"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā samiddhi acirapakkante potaliputte paribbājake yenāyasmā "
"ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Soon after he had left, Venerable Samiddhi went to Venerable Ānanda, and "
"exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "mn136:3.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "mn136:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā samiddhi yāvatako ahosi potaliputtena "
"paribbājakena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ āyasmato ānandassa ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed Ānanda of all they had discussed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ samiddhiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Ānanda said to him:"

msgctxt "mn136:3.5"
msgid "“atthi kho idaṃ, āvuso samiddhi, kathāpābhataṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya."
msgstr "“Reverend Samiddhi, we should see the Buddha about this matter."

msgctxt "mn136:3.6"
msgid ""
"Āyāmāvuso samiddhi, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā "
"etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocessāma."
msgstr "Come, let’s go to the Buddha and inform him about this."

msgctxt "mn136:3.7"
msgid "Yathā no bhagavā byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti."
msgstr "As he answers, so we’ll remember it.”"

msgctxt "mn136:3.8"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā samiddhi āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” Samiddhi replied."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ca ānando āyasmā ca samiddhi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then Ānanda and Samiddhi went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "mn136:4.2"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako ahosi āyasmato samiddhissa "
"potaliputtena paribbājakena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato "
"ārocesi."
msgstr "and told him what had happened."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When they had spoken, the Buddha said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "mn136:5.2"
msgid ""
"“dassanampi kho ahaṃ, ānanda, potaliputtassa paribbājakassa nābhijānāmi, "
"kuto panevarūpaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"“I don’t recall even seeing the wanderer Potaliputta, Ānanda, so how could "
"we have had such a discussion?"

msgctxt "mn136:5.3"
msgid ""
"Iminā ca, ānanda, samiddhinā moghapurisena potaliputtassa paribbājakassa "
"vibhajjabyākaraṇīyo pañho ekaṃsena byākato”ti."
msgstr ""
"The wanderer Potaliputta’s question should have been answered after "
"analyzing it, but this foolish person answered with a generalization.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Udāyī said to him:"

#. VAR: sace pana → kiṃ pana (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:6.2"
msgid "“sace pana, bhante, āyasmatā samiddhinā idaṃ sandhāya bhāsitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“But perhaps, sir, Venerable Samiddhi spoke in reference to the statement:"

msgctxt "mn136:6.3"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci vedayitaṃ taṃ dukkhasmin”ti."
msgstr "‘Suffering includes whatever is felt.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.209"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: Atha kho → evaṃ vutte (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn136:6.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda:"

# Ummagga is from ummujjati, just below, “uprising, emergence”.
#. VAR: ummaṅgaṃ → ummaggaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | umaṅgaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:6.5"
msgid "“passasi no tvaṃ, ānanda, imassa udāyissa moghapurisassa ummaṅgaṃ?"
msgstr "“See how this foolish person Udāyī comes up with an idea?"

msgctxt "mn136:6.6"
msgid "Aññāsiṃ kho ahaṃ, ānanda:"
msgstr "I knew that"

msgctxt "mn136:6.7"
msgid "‘idānevāyaṃ udāyī moghapuriso ummujjamāno ayoniso ummujjissatī’ti."
msgstr "he was going to come up with such an irrational idea."

#. VAR: Ādiṃyeva → ādisova (pts1) | ādiyeva (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:6.8"
msgid "Ādiṃyeva, ānanda, potaliputtena paribbājakena tisso vedanā pucchitā."
msgstr "Right from the start Potaliputta asked about the three feelings."

msgctxt "mn136:6.9"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, ānanda, samiddhi moghapuriso potaliputtassa paribbājakassa evaṃ "
"puṭṭho evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr ""
"Suppose the foolish person Samiddhi had answered the wanderer Potaliputta’s "
"question like this:"

msgctxt "mn136:6.10"
msgid ""
"‘sañcetanikaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, kammaṃ katvā kāyena vācāya manasā "
"sukhavedanīyaṃ sukhaṃ so vedayati;"
msgstr ""
"‘After doing an intentional deed to be experienced as pleasant by way of "
"body, speech, or mind, one feels pleasure."

msgctxt "mn136:6.11"
msgid ""
"sañcetanikaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, kammaṃ katvā kāyena vācāya manasā "
"dukkhavedanīyaṃ dukkhaṃ so vedayati;"
msgstr ""
"After doing an intentional deed to be experienced as painful by way of body, "
"speech, or mind, one feels pain."

msgctxt "mn136:6.12"
msgid ""
"sañcetanikaṃ, āvuso potaliputta, kammaṃ katvā kāyena vācāya manasā "
"adukkhamasukhavedanīyaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ so vedayatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"After doing an intentional deed to be experienced as neutral by way of body, "
"speech, or mind, one feels neutral.’"

#. VAR: byākaramāno → idaṃ padaṃ bj, s1-3, km, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "mn136:6.13"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, ānanda, samiddhi moghapuriso potaliputtassa "
"paribbājakassa sammā byākaramāno byākareyya."
msgstr ""
"Answering in this way, Samiddhi would have rightly answered Potaliputta."

#. VAR: ca → keci (mr)
msgctxt "mn136:6.14"
msgid ""
"Api ca, ānanda, ke ca aññatitthiyā paribbājakā bālā abyattā ke ca "
"tathāgatassa mahākammavibhaṅgaṃ jānissanti?"
msgstr ""
"Still, who are those foolish and incompetent wanderers who follow other "
"paths to understand the Realized One’s great analysis of deeds?"

# This specific phrasing is shared with MN 136 and AN 6.62. In both cases, the context follows a case where a junior monk has made a silly statement. I think the phrasing is meant to express a certain frustration, if I may dare to use such a term of the Buddha! The parsing of vibhajantassa is problematic, see BB’s note on AN 6.62.
msgctxt "mn136:6.15"
msgid ""
"Sace tumhe, ānanda, suṇeyyātha tathāgatassa mahākammavibhaṅgaṃ "
"vibhajantassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, if only you would all listen to the Realized One’s explanation of "
"the great analysis of deeds.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:7.1"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo, etassa, sugata, kālo "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "mn136:7.2"
msgid ""
"yaṃ bhagavā mahākammavibhaṅgaṃ vibhajeyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū "
"dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Let the Buddha explain the great analysis of deeds. The mendicants will "
"listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "mn136:7.3"
msgid "“Tena hānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn136:7.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "mn136:7.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:8.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, ānanda, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Ānanda, these four people are found in the world."

msgctxt "mn136:8.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "mn136:8.3"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, ekacco puggalo idha pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, "
"kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, "
"samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhi hoti."
msgstr ""
"Some person here kills living creatures, steals, and commits sexual "
"misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. "
"And they’re covetous, malicious, and have wrong view."

msgctxt "mn136:8.4"
msgid ""
"So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. "
"(1)"
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a "
"bad place, the underworld, hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:8.5"
msgid ""
"Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo idha pāṇātipātī hoti, adinnādāyī hoti, "
"kāmesumicchācārī hoti, musāvādī hoti, pisuṇavāco hoti, pharusavāco hoti, "
"samphappalāpī hoti, abhijjhālu hoti, byāpannacitto hoti, micchādiṭṭhi hoti."
msgstr ""
"But some other person here kills living creatures, steals, and commits "
"sexual misconduct. They use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or "
"nonsensical. And they’re covetous, malicious, and have wrong view."

msgctxt "mn136:8.6"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. (2)"
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.210"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:8.7"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, ekacco puggalo idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā "
"paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, "
"pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, "
"samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, "
"sammādiṭṭhi hoti."
msgstr ""
"But some other person here refrains from killing living creatures, stealing, "
"committing sexual misconduct, or using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, "
"or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, and have right view."

msgctxt "mn136:8.8"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. (3)"
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:8.9"
msgid ""
"Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā "
"paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, "
"pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, "
"samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, "
"sammādiṭṭhi hoti."
msgstr ""
"But some other person here refrains from killing living creatures, stealing, "
"committing sexual misconduct, or using speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, "
"or nonsensical. And they’re contented, kind-hearted, and have right view."

msgctxt "mn136:8.10"
msgid ""
"So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati. "
"(4)"
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a "
"bad place, the underworld, hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:9.1"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati yathāsamāhite citte dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena amuṃ puggalaṃ passati—"
msgstr ""
"Now, some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of "
"such a kind that it gives rise to clairvoyance that is purified and "
"superhuman. With that clairvoyance they see that person"

msgctxt "mn136:9.2"
msgid ""
"idha pāṇātipātiṃ adinnādāyiṃ kāmesumicchācāriṃ musāvādiṃ pisuṇavācaṃ "
"pharusavācaṃ samphappalāpiṃ abhijjhāluṃ byāpannacittaṃ micchādiṭṭhiṃ kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā passati apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ."
msgstr ""
"here who killed living creatures, stole, and committed sexual misconduct; "
"who used speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and who was "
"covetous, malicious, and had wrong view. And they see that, when their body "
"breaks up, after death, that person is reborn in a place of loss, a bad "
"place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "mn136:9.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "mn136:9.4"
msgid "‘atthi kira, bho, pāpakāni kammāni, atthi duccaritassa vipāko."
msgstr ""
"‘It seems that there is such a thing as bad deeds, and the result of bad "
"conduct."

#. VAR: Amāhaṃ → apāhaṃ (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn136:9.5"
msgid ""
"Amāhaṃ puggalaṃ addasaṃ idha pāṇātipātiṃ adinnādāyiṃ … pe … micchādiṭṭhiṃ "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā passāmi apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapannan’ti."
msgstr ""
"For I saw a person here who killed living creatures … and had wrong view. "
"And when their body broke up, after death, they were reborn in a place of "
"loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’"

