"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati, "
msgstr ""
"Now, Ānanda, take the case of the person here who killed living creatures … "
"and had wrong view, and who, when their body breaks up, after death, is "
"reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "mn136:17.2"
msgid ""
"pubbe vāssa taṃ kataṃ hoti pāpakammaṃ dukkhavedanīyaṃ, pacchā vāssa taṃ "
"kataṃ hoti pāpakammaṃ dukkhavedanīyaṃ, maraṇakāle vāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi "
"samattā samādinnā."
msgstr ""
"They must have done a bad deed to be experienced as painful either "
"previously or later, or else at the time of death they undertook wrong view."

msgctxt "mn136:17.3"
msgid ""
"Tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And that’s why, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "mn136:17.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho so idha pāṇātipātī hoti adinnādāyī hoti … pe … micchādiṭṭhi hoti "
"tassa diṭṭheva dhamme vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye. "
"(1)"
msgstr ""
"But anyone here who kills living creatures … and has wrong view experiences "
"the result of that in the present life, or in the next life, or in some "
"subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:18.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, yvāyaṃ puggalo idha pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī … pe … micchādiṭṭhi "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati, "
msgstr ""
"Now, Ānanda, take the case of the person here who killed living creatures … "
"and had wrong view, and who is reborn in a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "mn136:18.2"
msgid ""
"pubbe vāssa taṃ kataṃ hoti kalyāṇakammaṃ sukhavedanīyaṃ, pacchā vāssa taṃ "
"kataṃ hoti kalyāṇakammaṃ sukhavedanīyaṃ, maraṇakāle vāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi "
"samattā samādinnā."
msgstr ""
"They must have done a good deed to be experienced as pleasant either "
"previously or later, or else at the time of death they undertook right view."

msgctxt "mn136:18.3"
msgid "Tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And that’s why, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "mn136:18.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho so idha pāṇātipātī hoti adinnādāyī hoti … pe … micchādiṭṭhi hoti "
"tassa diṭṭheva dhamme vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye. "
"(2)"
msgstr ""
"But anyone here who kills living creatures … and has wrong view experiences "
"the result of that in the present life, or in the next life, or in some "
"subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.215"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:19.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, yvāyaṃ puggalo idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato adinnādānā paṭivirato …"
" pe … sammādiṭṭhi, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjati, "
msgstr ""
"Now, Ānanda, take the case of the person here who refrained from killing "
"living creatures … and had right view, and who is reborn in a heavenly "
"realm. "

msgctxt "mn136:19.2"
msgid ""
"pubbe vāssa taṃ kataṃ hoti kalyāṇakammaṃ sukhavedanīyaṃ, pacchā vāssa taṃ "
"kataṃ hoti kalyāṇakammaṃ sukhavedanīyaṃ, maraṇakāle vāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi "
"samattā samādinnā."
msgstr ""
"They must have done a good deed to be experienced as pleasant either "
"previously or later, or else at the time of death they undertook right view."

msgctxt "mn136:19.3"
msgid "Tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And that’s why, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "mn136:19.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho so idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti … pe "
"… sammādiṭṭhi hoti, tassa diṭṭheva dhamme vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti upapajja vā "
"apare vā pariyāye. (3)"
msgstr ""
"But anyone here who refrains from killing living creatures … and has right "
"view experiences the result of that in the present life, or in the next "
"life, or in some subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:20.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, yvāyaṃ puggalo idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato adinnādānā paṭivirato …"
" pe … sammādiṭṭhi, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapajjati, "
msgstr ""
"Now, Ānanda, take the case of the person here who refrained from killing "
"living creatures … and had right view, and who is reborn in hell. "

msgctxt "mn136:20.2"
msgid ""
"pubbe vāssa taṃ kataṃ hoti pāpakammaṃ dukkhavedanīyaṃ, pacchā vāssa taṃ "
"kataṃ hoti pāpakammaṃ dukkhavedanīyaṃ, maraṇakāle vāssa hoti micchādiṭṭhi "
"samattā samādinnā."
msgstr ""
"They must have done a bad deed to be experienced as painful either "
"previously or later, or else at the time of death they undertook wrong view."

msgctxt "mn136:20.3"
msgid ""
"Tena so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And that’s why, when their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "mn136:20.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho so idha pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti … "
"pe … sammādiṭṭhi hoti, tassa diṭṭheva dhamme vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti upapajja "
"vā apare vā pariyāye. (4)"
msgstr ""
"But anyone here who refrains from killing living creatures … and has right "
"view experiences the result of that in the present life, or in the next "
"life, or in some subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:21.1"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, ānanda, atthi kammaṃ abhabbaṃ abhabbābhāsaṃ, atthi kammaṃ abhabbaṃ "
"bhabbābhāsaṃ, atthi kammaṃ bhabbañceva bhabbābhāsañca, atthi kammaṃ bhabbaṃ "
"abhabbābhāsan”ti."
msgstr ""
"So, Ānanda, there are deeds that are ineffective and appear ineffective. "
"There are deeds that are ineffective but appear effective. There are deeds "
"that are effective and appear effective. And there are deeds that are "
"effective but appear ineffective.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn136:21.2"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn136:21.3"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn136:21.4"
msgid "Mahākammavibhaṅgasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
